The paper discusses the use of a nature-inspired algorithm (firefly algorithm) for training a neural network, which falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE). The paper also discusses the use of back-propagation, which is a common technique in machine learning (cs.LG). Additionally, the paper discusses the use of meta-heuristic algorithms, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and swarm intelligence (cs.SI). Finally, the paper discusses the use of nature-inspired algorithms, which falls under the category of nature-inspired computing (cs.NI).
